<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Loyalty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Loyalty,</orth> dutifulness, fidelity; in love: <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 102</bibl>. in the condition of a subject: <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 4, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.203" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 203</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.250" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 250</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.239" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 239</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.239" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 239</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 3, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.177" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 4, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 5, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 5, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.344" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 344</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.3.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 3, 92</bibl>. of a servant: <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 3, 70</bibl>. Plur. <emph>--s</emph>: <cit><quote>flawed the heart of all their --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 22</bibl></cit>. With <cit><quote>to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 7</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 42</bibl>. With <cit><quote>toward:</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.272" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 272</bibl></cit>.
